---
import LayoutFunnel from '@/layouts/LayoutFunnel.astro';
---

<LayoutFunnel title="Restaurant Revenue Architecture | Marketing by Besic">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-4xl text-center">
      <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-brand/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-8">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-brand" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
        </svg>
      </div>

      <h1 class="heading-xl mb-6">
        Your 3.8-Star Rating Is Costing You EUR 50K Per Year. Here's the Fix.
      </h1>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        Legacy bad reviews don't just hurt your pride. They suppress your Google ranking, reduce click-through, and send customers to the competitor down the street -- permanently.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Image -->
      <img src="/offer-restaurant-hero.webp" alt="Restaurant Revenue Architecture" class="w-full rounded-lg mb-12 object-cover max-h-[500px]" width="1200" height="500" loading="eager" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Three Revenue Leaks Killing Your Restaurant</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 1: Legacy Bad Reviews Dragging Down Every Location</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            That 2-star review from 2021 is still on page one of your Google Business Profile. It's not ancient history -- it's actively costing you reservations every single day. Potential customers see it, form an opinion, and scroll past. You never even knew they existed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 2: No Systematic Review Generation</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            You rely on happy customers remembering to post. They don't. The customers who DO remember to post are the angry ones. Without a systematic review generation protocol triggered at the right moment in the dining experience, your reputation is determined by your worst nights, not your best.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 3: Marketing Disconnected from Operations</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            Your ads bring people in. But the in-restaurant experience doesn't match the promise. Your Instagram says "fine dining experience." Your server is overwhelmed because no one coordinated with the marketing schedule. The result: one-time visitors, not regulars.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem Image -->
      <img src="/offer-restaurant-problem.webp" alt="Restaurant revenue leak diagnosis" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Solution Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">The Reputation Revenue Architecture</h2>

      <!-- Phase 1 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 1: Reputation Architecture Diagnostic</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              We map every review source, identify suppression opportunities, and benchmark your reputation against direct competitors. You'll see exactly how many covers per month your current rating is costing you -- quantified, not guessed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 2 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 2: Systematic Review Generation + GMB Optimization</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Review generation protocols triggered at the peak satisfaction moment. Response templates that turn negative reviews into reputation assets. Google My Business optimization across every location. This isn't "please leave us a review" -- it's behavioral engineering.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 3 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 3: Multi-Location Marketing System</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Each location managed, monitored, and optimized independently. Marketing schedules coordinated with operations. Revenue tracked per location, per campaign, per channel. No more guessing which location is underperforming or why.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution Image -->
      <img src="/offer-restaurant-solution.webp" alt="Reputation Revenue Architecture system" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution Gap Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#111111] relative z-10">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Most Agencies Deliver Reports. We Deliver Revenue.</h2>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center">
        The gap between knowing your reputation problem and fixing it is where restaurant groups bleed out slowly. Your last consultant gave you a "reputation management strategy." Your rating didn't move. Our framework closes the execution gap by building the systems, training the triggers, and tracking the results.
      </p>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center font-semibold text-brand">
        We scaled Koykan from 1 country to 4 while maintaining 4.6+ star ratings across every location.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-20 pb-48">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-6">Apply for a Revenue Diagnosis</h2>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        We work with restaurant groups generating EUR 1M+ annually across 2+ locations. If your reputation is suppressing your revenue, apply below.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-center w-full">
        <a
          href="/en/apply"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold text-white transition-all duration-300 bg-[#8224e3] rounded-lg hover:bg-[#6a1ca6] hover:scale-105 shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(130,36,227,0.4)]"
        >
          Apply for Revenue Diagnosis
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LayoutFunnel>
